newsitem.title: THAILAND: Thai interbank rate down, baht steady late.
newsitem.headline: Thai interbank rate down, baht steady late.

text.p: The Thai overnight interbank rate eased to 7.00 percent in early trade on Friday from 7.50-8.00 percent late on Thursday on higher liquidity, dealers said.
"The money supply remained high today as banks continued to lend surplus funds after the passing of reserve requirement yesterday," said a dealer at a foreign bank.
A dealer at a European bank said the money supply was expected to be fall next week due to corporate tax payments which are made every two months.
The baht was steady at 25.304-25.309 to the dollar in late trade compared with 25.305-25.310 in the morning.
The one-month swap premium was at 6.20/7.00 satangs late compared with 6.75/7.50 late on Thursday, dealers said.
The Bank of Thailand fixed the mid-rate at 25.31 to the dollar compared with 25.30 on Thursday.
